description:
The refurbishment of 114-116 and 122-124  the demolition
and rebuilding of 118-120 and the erection of a 5 storey
building at No. 112  together with the refurbishment or
rebuilding three storey link blocks to provide 63
residential units; also the reconstruction and
extension of the perimeter wall with the provision of
car parking (25 spaces); as shown on drawing nos.
91/371/P01  P02B  P03B  P04C  P05A  P06A  P07  P08A
P09A  P11A  P12A  P13  P14  P15  P16  T02A  as revised
by letters dated 10.12.92  23.12.92  and 01.03.93.
decision_conditions:
Condition : 1 - Revised details of the design of the elevations and facing
    materials to be used on the new building at 112 Haverstock
    Hill and the new link blocks, shall be submitted to and
    approved by the Council before any work on the site is
    commenced and the development shall not be otherwise than
    in accordance with such details.

Condition : 2 - The whole of the carparking shown on the approved plans
    shall be provided and retained permanently for the parking
    of vehicles of the occupiers of and visitors to the
    dwellings approved.

Condition : 3 - No development shall take place until full details of hard
    and soft landscaping and means of enclosure of all unbuilt,
    open areas have been submitted to and approved by the
    Council.

Condition : 4 - All hard and soft landscaping works shall be carried out to
    later than the end of the following planting season, with
    others of similar size and species, unless the Council
    gives written consent to any variation.
    a reasonable standard in accordance with the approved
    landscape details by not later than the end of the planting
    season following completion of the development or any phase
    of the development, whichever is the sooner. Any trees or
    areas of planting which, within a period of 5 years from
    the completion of the development, die, are removed, or
    become seriously damaged or diseased, shall be replaced as
    soon as is reasonably possible and, in any case, by not

Condition : 5 - All trees on the site, or parts of trees growing from

    reasonably possible and, in any case, by not later than the
    end of the following planting season, with trees of such
    size and species and in such positions as may be agreed
    with the Council, without prejudice to any further action
    the Council may consider appropriate to secure the
    protection of existing trees.

Condition : 6 - To ensure that the Council may be satisfied with the
    external appearance of the new buildings.

Condition : 7 - To ensure the permanent retention of the area for parking
    purposes and to ensure that the use of the building does
    not add to traffic generation.

Condition : 8 - In order that the Council may give consideration to the
    details of the proposed scheme.

Condition : 9 - To ensure that the landscaping is carried out within a
    reasonable period and to maintain a satisfactory standard
    of visual amenity in the scheme.

Condition : 10 - To ensure that the Council may be satisfied that the
    development will not have an adverse effect on existing
    trees and in order to maintain the character and amenities
    of the area.

Condition : 11 - The enclosed leaflet sets out the Council's guidelines for
    the protection of trees on development sites.
